DEBUG (pocknix, TEMPORARY — remove after confirming the Layer-3 wake source): log
every pmic_glink message the battery manager receives, with its opcode. After a
suspend cycle, `dmesg | grep wakedbg` shows what arrived right after "PM: suspend
exit" — i.e. the opcode of the ADSP message that woke the device. 0x7 =
BATTMGR_NOTIFICATION (the charger firmware's unsolicited status push). If NOTHING is
logged at the wake, the wake is a different pmic_glink owner (UCSI/altmode) or another
ADSP service, and we look there instead. See docs/sm8550-suspend-wake-report.md (Layer 3).

NOTE: this lives directly in pocknix's kernel/patches/20-sm8550/ (not the ROCKNIX
fork), so it is a throwaway — `make sync` will delete it (rsync --delete). Build with
`make kernel` directly; do NOT `make sync` first or it vanishes.
---
 drivers/power/supply/qcom_battmgr.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/power/supply/qcom_battmgr.c
+++ b/drivers/power/supply/qcom_battmgr.c
@@ -1572,6 +1572,7 @@ static void qcom_battmgr_callback(const void *data, size_t len, void *priv)
 	const struct pmic_glink_hdr *hdr = data;
 	struct qcom_battmgr *battmgr = priv;
 	unsigned int opcode = le32_to_cpu(hdr->opcode);
+	dev_info(battmgr->dev, "pocknix-wakedbg: rx opcode %#x\n", opcode);

 	if (opcode == BATTMGR_NOTIFICATION)
 		qcom_battmgr_notification(battmgr, data, len);
